        <section>
          <code code="34084-4" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" displayName="ADVERSE REACTIONS"/>
          <title>ADVERSE REACTIONS</title>
          <text>
            <paragraph>The following adverse reactions have been reported during use of propofol:</paragraph>
            <paragraph>Cardiac disorders: Bradycardia, Cardiac arrest, Tachycardia</paragraph>
            <paragraph>Vascular disorders: Hypotension, Hypertension</paragraph>
            <paragraph>Respiratory disorders: Apnea, Respiratory depression, Bronchospasm</paragraph>
            <paragraph>Nervous system disorders: Headache, Dizziness, Involuntary movements</paragraph>
            <paragraph>Gastrointestinal disorders: Nausea, Vomiting</paragraph>
            <paragraph>General disorders: Pain at injection site, Fever</paragraph>
            <paragraph>Metabolic disorders: Hypertriglyceridemia, Metabolic acidosis</paragraph>
            <paragraph>Immune system disorders: Anaphylaxis, Anaphylactoid reaction</paragraph>
          </text>
        </section>
      </component>
      <component>
        <section>
          <code code="34068-7" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" displayName="DOSAGE AND ADMINISTRATION"/>
          <title>DOSAGE AND ADMINISTRATION</title>
          <text>
            <paragraph>Propofol is an intravenous anesthetic agent.</paragraph>
          </text>
        </section>
      </component>
